Regling Says Markets Trust in the Euro Again, Standard Reports

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-04-01T16:35:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/regling-says-markets-trust-in-the-euro-again-standard-reports.html
Klaus Regling, head of the rescue
fund for debt-laden euro countries, said financial markets have
regained trust in the euro as the currency bloc has reached “a
turning point,”  Der Standard  reported, citing an interview.  “The situation and the problems of the euro have changed
significantly,” Regling was quoted as  saying . “Markets do not
believe anymore that the euro could disappear,” Regling said,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
